On January 2, 2013, the President signed into law H.R. 4310, the "National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2013." This act authorizes appropriations for various defense programs and military construction, national security programs, and maritime security programs. It also authorizes recruitment and retention bonuses, special payments, and other authorities relating to the U.S. Armed Forces. Additionally, the act includes modifications to national security, foreign affairs, and other related programs.